title: China hoped Fiji would be a template for the Pacific. Its plan backfired.
description: China used Fiji as a testing ground for pursuing closer security ties in the Pacific. But Beijing over reached, and the new government is tearing up the deal.

title: 10 years after deadly chemical attack, Syria’s survivors seek justice
description: The sarin-filled rockets that fell on Damascus in August 2013 killed over 1,400 people. A mountain of evidence implicating Syria’s government continues to grow.

title: British nurse who killed 7 babies sentenced to life in prison
description: Lucy Letby was found guilty of killing the seven infants and of attempting to kill six more.

title: Spain’s soccer president condemned for kissing player on the lips
description: Those watching the World Cup medal ceremony after Spain’s win condemned Luis Rubiales for kissing Jenni Hermoso on the lips.

title: Who gets to curate ‘David’? In Italy, the culture wars get a nationalist edge.
description: Italy’s new right-wing government is adopting a process that critics say injects nationalism into hiring decisions about who will run museums.

title: Ukraine live briefing: Zelensky hails ‘historic’ pledge of F-16s from Netherlands, Denmark
description: Copenhagen and Amsterdam agreed to deliver 61 of the fighter jets to Kyiv when conditions such as successful testing and training are met.

title: How Ukraine is exploiting Biden’s cluster bomb gamble
description: The widely banned munition is wreaking havoc on Russian infantry, but concerns about unexploded ordnance remain.

title: Saudi forces killed hundreds of Ethiopians at Yemen border, report says
description: The killings, which have been both widespread and systematic, could qualify as crimes against humanity, Human Rights Watch says.

title: Ukraine’s hopes for maximal victory look remote
description: The reality of Ukraine’s difficult fight against Russia has led to some unusually blunt admissions.
